#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/Ignition/Ignition.rst:94
msgid "2 Configuring ROS 2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/Ignition/Ignition.rst:96
msgid ""
"To be able to communicate our simulation with ROS 2 you need to use a "
"package called ``ros_ign_bridge``. This package provides a network bridge "
"which enables the exchange of messages between ROS 2 and Ignition Transport. "
"You can install this package by typing:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/Ignition/Ignition.rst:104
msgid "sudo apt-get install ros-rolling-ros-ign-bridge"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/Ignition/Ignition.rst:108
msgid ""
"At this point you are ready to launch a bridge from ROS to Ignition. In "
"particular you are going to create a bridge for the topic ``/model/"
"vehicle_blue/cmd_vel``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/Ignition/Ignition.rst:115
msgid ""
"source /opt/ros/rolling/setup.bash\n"
"ros2 run ros_ign_bridge parameter_bridge /model/vehicle_blue/"
"cmd_vel@geometry_msgs/msg/Twist]ignition.msgs.Twist"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/Ignition/Ignition.rst:120
msgid ""
"For more details about the ``ros_ign_bridge`` please check this `README "
"<https://github.com/gazebosim/ros_gz/tree/ros2/ros_gz_bridge>`__ ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/Ignition/Ignition.rst:122
msgid ""
"Once the bridge is running the robot is able to follow your motor commands. "
"There are two options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/Ignition/Ignition.rst:125
msgid "Send a command to the topic using ``ros2 topic pub``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/Ignition/Ignition.rst:131
msgid ""
"ros2 topic pub /model/vehicle_blue/cmd_vel geometry_msgs/Twist  \"linear: "
"{ x: 0.1 }\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/Ignition/Ignition.rst:135
msgid ""
"``teleop_twist_keyboard`` package. This node takes keypresses from the "
"keyboard and publishes them as Twist messages. You can install it typing:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/Ignition/Ignition.rst:141
msgid "sudo apt-get install ros-rolling-teleop-twist-keyboard"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/Ignition/Ignition.rst:145
msgid ""
"The default topic where ``teleop_twist_keyboard`` is publishing Twist "
"messages is ``/cmd_vel`` but you can remap this topic to make use of the "
"topic used in the bridge:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/Ignition/Ignition.rst:152
msgid ""
"source /opt/ros/rolling/setup.bash\n"
"ros2 run teleop_twist_keyboard teleop_twist_keyboard --ros-args -r /cmd_vel:"
"=/model/vehicle_blue/cmd_vel\n"
"\n"
"This node takes keypresses from the keyboard and publishes them\n"
"as Twist messages. It works best with a US keyboard layout.\n"
"---------------------------\n"
"Moving around:\n"
"   u    i    o\n"
"   j    k    l\n"
"   m    ,    .\n"
"\n"
"For Holonomic mode (strafing), hold down the shift key:\n"
"---------------------------\n"
"   U    I    O\n"
"   J    K    L\n"
"   M    <    >\n"
"\n"
"t : up (+z)\n"
"b : down (-z)\n"
"\n"
"anything else : stop\n"
"\n"
"q/z : increase/decrease max speeds by 10%\n"
"w/x : increase/decrease only linear speed by 10%\n"
"e/c : increase/decrease only angular speed by 10%\n"
"\n"
"CTRL-C to quit\n"
"\n"
"currently:      speed 0.5       turn 1.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/Ignition/Ignition.rst:185
msgid "3 Visualizing lidar data in ROS 2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/Ignition/Ignition.rst:187
msgid ""
"The diff drive robot has a lidar. To send the data generated by Ignition to "
"ROS 2, you need to launch another bridge. In the case the data from the "
"lidar is provided in the Ignition Transport topic ``/lidar2``, which you are "
"going to remap in the bridge. This topic will be available under the topic "
"``/lidar_scan``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/Ignition/Ignition.rst:197
msgid ""
"source /opt/ros/rolling/setup.bash\n"
"ros2 run ros_ign_bridge parameter_bridge /lidar2@sensor_msgs/msg/"
"LaserScan[ignition.msgs.LaserScan --ros-args -r /lidar2:=/laser_scan"
msgstr ""

